- Classes are a definition explaining to the program about the attributes and actions of a particular noun. 

- Fields = adjectives (description) 
- Methods = verb (action) 

Examples of classes: 
- Strings - Methods: length(), compareTo(String)
- User - Fields: name, birthday, tagline
        Methods: followUser(user)
- Book - Fields: title, ISBN, numPages
         Methods: exportPDF(fileName)
         
Example (simple class for 'User'): 

public class User {
  // fields 

  String name; 
  String pitrureURL; 
  String email; 
  
  // methods
  
  public void printName() {
    System.out.println("My name is: " + name); 
  } 
}

